---

{# ── STATE ROUTER · the B5 signature. Selector (built-out → pillar, else → contact)
     + the 5 built-out state pillars as a routing grid. Data-driven (allStates/states),
     scales to 50 states. (H2: Find an accountant by state.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="faa-states">
  <div class="ct">
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:baseline;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px;margin-bottom:10px;">
      <div class="idx" style="margin-bottom:0;"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Routing by state</span></div>
      <span class="mono" style="font-size:12.5px;color:var(--color-ink-faint);">5 states built out &middot; every other state served remotely</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:26ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Find an accountant by state.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 26px;max-width:66ch;">Pick your state to route straight to the right page &mdash; or browse the built-out states below. Each state page is built around what&rsquo;s actually different there: the local taxes, the filing realities, the industries.</p>
    <div class="state-router" style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;align-items:flex-end;margin-bottom:30px;">
      <label style="flex:1;min-width:240px;"><span style="display:block;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:var(--color-ink);margin-bottom:7px;">Pick your state</span>
        <select id="faa-state-select" aria-label="Choose your state to find an accountant" style="width:100%;min-height:48px;padding:11px 13px;background:var(--white);border:1px solid var(--border-default);border-radius:10px;font:inherit;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--color-ink);">
          <option value="" selected>Choose your state&hellip;</option>
          {%- for s in allStates %}
          <option value="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name }}{% if s.built %} &mdash; dedicated page{% endif %}</option>
          {%- endfor %}
        </select>
      </label>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn-cta" id="faa-state-go" style="height:48px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:11px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Find my accountant</button>
    </div>
    <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Built-out states</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in states %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ s.tag }}</span><h3><a href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }}</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.note | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.name | safe }} accountants <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
      {%- endfor %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">Every other state</span><h3><a href="/contact/?intent=find-an-accountant">Served remotely &mdash; tell us where you are</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">We serve businesses in every state remotely on QuickBooks. Tell us your state and what you need, and a Certified ProAdvisor will route you.</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="/contact/?intent=find-an-accountant">Tell us where you are <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT YOU GET · numbered value props (dc-card r-4). (H2: What you get, in any state.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="faa-value">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What you get</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:28px;">What you get, in any state.</h2>
    <div class="r-4">
      {%- for v in valueProps %}
      <div class="dc-card"><div class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--color-accent);margin-bottom:12px;">0{{ loop.index }}</div><h3 style="font-size:16px;">{{ v.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ v.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ROUTE BY NEED · silo routing (QuickBooks → /quickbooks/, accounting → /accounting/,
     start → file-review). The hub routes to the RIGHT silo. (H2: Or start with what you need.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="faa-needs" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Routing by need</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Or start with what you need.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:60ch;">Know the work already? Go straight to the right silo.</p>
    <div class="r-4">
      {%- for n in needs %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ n.opener | safe }}</span><h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.name | safe }}</a></h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.cta | safe }}</a></article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── NETWORK · the honest model, dc-card r-3 + disclosure note. (H2: How the network works.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="faa-network">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Direct delivery + vetted partners</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:28px;">How the network works.</h2>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for n in network %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ n.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:24px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">TechBrot is an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc. It provides bookkeeping and operational accounting and coordinates with your CPA or EA, who files tax returns and represents you before tax authorities.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# State router: route to the selected state's destination. Progressive enhancement —
   the built-out grid above covers no-JS users. #}
<script>
(function(){var s=document.getElementById("faa-state-select"),b=document.getElementById("faa-state-go");if(!s||!b)return;function go(){if(s.value){window.location.href=s.value;}}b.addEventListener("click",go);s.addEventListener("keydown",function(e){if(e.key==="Enter"){go();}});})();
</script>
